title: Appointments to Social Welfare Advisory Committee
content_text:
p>The Government announced today (November 25) the appointment of four new members 
and the re-appointment of four incumbent members to the Social Welfare Advisory 
Committee (SWAC). All the appointments are for a term of two years with effect 
from December 1 this year.  The four new members are: Prof Japhet Sebastian Law; Mr Timothy Ma Kam-wah, Prof 
Tang Kwong-leung; and Dr Jimmy Wong Chi-ho. Prof Law is the professor of Department of Decision Science and Managerial

Economic of the Chinese University of Hong Kong. As the chairman of a non-subvented 
agency, he is familiar with the welfare sector. He is also serving on the Air 
Transport Licensing Authority. Mr Ma is the executive director of a non-subvented welfare agency. He is 
familiar with the welfare sector and serving on the Guardianship Board under the 
Social Welfare Department. Prof Tang is the professor and chair of Social Work Department of the Chinese 
University of Hong Kong. He has both frontline and academic experience in the

University of Hong Kong. He has both frontline and academic experience in the 
welfare field and has provided useful advice to the Social Welfare Department on 
various matters. Dr Wong is the president of Tung Chun Group. He is very active in the social 
service field and has served as the chairman and vice-chairman of various major 
welfare agencies. He is also a member of the Advisory Committee of the 
Partnership Fund for the Disadvantaged. Meanwhile, four incumbent members have been re-appointed. They are: Dr Miranda

Chung Chan Lai-foon, Ms Christine Fang Meng-sang, Ms Marina Wong Yu-pok, and Mr 
Silva Yeung Tak-wah. The Secretary for Health, Welfare and Food, Dr York Chow, welcomed the 
appointment of the new members and the re-appointment of the incumbent members. 
He looked forward to their contribution to the development of welfare policy 
issues. Dr Chow also thanked the four outgoing members �V Dr Joe Leung Cho-bun, Prof

Diana Mak Ping-see, Mr Aaron Wan Chi-keung, and Ms Jessie Yu Sau-chu - for their 
valuable advice to the SWAC during their term of appointment. The functions of the SWAC are to keep social welfare services under continuous 
review, and to advise the Government on all matters of social welfare policy. Following is the membership list of the SWAC as from December 1, 2005:
